(279, 85, 'descricao', 'The course called PLASTICADCAM is an immersion in the world of digital adhesive occlusal rehabilitation. Knowledge and experience of clinical occlusion associated with prosthetic virtualization technology. The proposed process for oral rehabilitation. A post-specialization aimed at the education and training of dentists who wish to master the technique and the logic of a computerized occlusal rehabilitation.\r\n\r\nThe title is a reference to the Association of Plastic Occlusal technique with the system design and manufacturing assisted by computer (Computer-Aided Design and Computer-Aided Manufacturing). The system used is the CEREC Sirona. During the course, students will learn how to rehabilitate a damaged occlusion using plastic methods and then learn how to make the replacement of plastic rehabilitation for prosthetic rehabilitation fully made in CEREC.\r\n\r\nA compact and intense, the course runs from Sunday to Saturday with hours ranging from 8 to 10 hours daily.'),
